{"CHECK":[{"def":"A word of warning denoting that the king is in danger; such a menace of a player's king by an adversary's move as would, if it were any other piece, expose it to immediate capture.","pos":""},{"def":"The forsaking by a hawk of its proper game to follow other birds.","pos":""}],"CHECKAGE":[{"def":"The act of checking; as, the checkage of a name or of an item in a list.","pos":""},{"def":"The items, or the amount, to which attention is called by a check or checks.","pos":""}],"CHECKER":[{"def":"To mark with small squares like a checkerboard, as by crossing stripes of different colors.","pos":""},{"def":"To variegate or diversify with different qualities, color, scenes, or events; esp.","pos":""}],"CHECKERBERRY":[{"def":"A spicy plant and its bright red berry; the wintergreen (Gaultheria procumbens).","pos":""}],"CHECKERBOARD":[{"def":"A board with sixty-four squares of alternate color, used for playing checkers or draughts.","pos":""}],"CHECKERED":[{"def":"Marked with alternate squares or checks of different color or material.","pos":""},{"def":"Diversified or variegated in a marked manner, as in appearance, character, circumstances, etc.","pos":""}],"CHECKERS":[{"def":"A game, called also daughts, played on a checkerboard by two persons, each having twelve men (counters or checkers) which are moved diagonally.","pos":""}],"CHECKERWORK":[{"def":"Work consisting of or showing checkers varied alternately as to colors or materials.","pos":""},{"def":"Any aggregate of varied vicissitudes.","pos":""}],"CHECKLESS":[{"def":"That can not be checked or restrained.","pos":""}],"CHECKMATE":[{"def":"The position in the game of chess when a king is in check and cannot be released, -- which ends the game.","pos":""},{"def":"A complete check; utter defeat or overthrow.","pos":""}],"CHECKREIN":[{"def":"A short rein looped over the check hook to prevent a horse from lowering his head; -- called also a bearing rein.","pos":""},{"def":"A branch rein connecting the driving rein of one horse of a span or pair with the bit of the other horse.","pos":""}],"CHECKROLL":[{"def":"A list of servants in a household; -- called also chequer roll.","pos":""}],"CHECKSTRING":[{"def":"A cord by which a person in a carriage or horse car may signal to the driver.","pos":""}],"CHECKWORK":[{"def":"Anything made so as to form alternate squares lke those of a checkerboard.","pos":""}],"CHECKY":[{"def":"Divided into small alternating squares of two tinctures; -- said of the field or of an armorial bearing.","pos":""}]}